definition:
The stochastic process $\{ Z_t, t \in T \}$,where T is the set of
natural integers $\mathbb{N}$ or the set of all integers $\mathbb{Z}$,
is said to be white noise with mean 0 and variance $\sigma^2$, written
$\{ Z_t\}\sim WN(0,\sigma^2)$, if and only if $\{ Z_t\}$ has zero mean
and autocovariance function $$\gamma\left(h\right) =
\left\{ 
\begin{array}{ll} 
\sigma^2 & \textrm{if } h=0 \\
0 & \textrm{if } h\neq 0  \end{array}
\right.$$
